Most counties will be sunny today with temperatures ranging from 27 degrees to 37 degrees, the Kenya Meteorological Department has said. In Nairobi, temperatures will rise to 28 degrees while Nyeri will have the lowest at 27 degrees. In the afternoon, Garissa and Wajir will have the highest temperatures at 37 degrees. Kitale will record 31 degrees from 11 in the morning. The sun is expected to set at 6.51 pm in Nairobi, Mombasa at 6.43 pm, Kisumu at 6.57 pm and Nakuru at 6.53 pm. Read: Sunny weather to persist in most counties - Weatherman Click here for the latest political news 